deck_excerpt: This deck is all about using Melffy and friends to save the forest!
deck_description: This deck is all about using Melffy and friends to save the forest!   Hide-and Seek!: You ALWAYS want to get out Melffy of the Forest and use it to grab Melffy Hide-and-Seek as soon as possible. Hide-and-Seek, other than being Melffys favorite game, allows you to save your beast monsters from being destroyed by card effects the first time each turn. It also allows you to shuffle three beasts with different names into your deck from your GY and draw a card. Melffy of the Forest lets you search cards, but also allows you to cancel the effects of a summoned monster once per turn if it activates a Melffy's ability to go back to your hand. This is why you should always have at least one Melffy monster out at all times. (which is VERY easy to do!)   The Melffys!: You pretty much always want to have Melffy Puppy out. This lets you grab Kalantosa, Mystical Beast of the Forest, activating its ability to destroy a card on the field. Melffy Catty lets you search cards you need to add to your hand. This very useful to grab a Rescue Cat or the Boss, Alpacaribou, Mystical Beast of the Forest. Melffy Fenny lets you summon from your hand completing the combo to get out Alpacaribou or any other monster stuck in your hand. Melffy Pony and Melffy Rabbi are mostly just fuel for Obedience Schooled or Xyz. Melffy Mommy is interesting and can be utilized really well for direct damage, a wall or Melffy Playhouse.   ...and Friends!: Naturia Beast is what you will mostly use Rescue Cat for summoning Valerifawn, Mystical Beast of the Forest and either Mine Mole or Crusadia Leonis to syncro for Naturia Beast in one turn. Nimble Beaver helps you get out your Xyz and I have subbed them for Amazoness Pet Baby Tiger which works better for Obedience Schooled (and keeps everyone EARTH) Missus Radiant is your go to for Link summoning. The attack boost is a huge help and with the help of Scapegoat you can summon both at once for little effort! Number 64: Ronin Raccoon Sandayu is a big help against foes with a lot attack power. It's tokens can fight the toughest boss monsters and with the help of Missus Radiant, Closed Forest, or Ayers rock Sunrise you can overtake them easily! Melffy Mommy has a huge pocket that works sort of like a bag of holding. She likes to turn it inside out for a Dark Hole magic attack that, if Melffy Hide-and-Seek is active, only gets rid of your opponents monsters! Aussa the Earth Charmer, Immovable likes to wander into the forest every once in awhile, but mostly to chase random creatures around for fun   I hope I covered everything! This deck is all about getting cards on and off the field and being cute and having fun! Though sometimes you need some protecting from the guardians of the forest. NOTE: I just got Joyous Melffys and I haven't played with it yet, but wanted it in there anyway

deck_excerpt: Constantly revive your Archfiends and use the Extra Deck for additional destruction!
deck_description: Hey! It's the Archfiend Guy Again :D  This deck is all about beatdown and stun! At its core, we summon high attack level 8 fiend monsters such as Archfiend Empress and Curse Necrofear, to help overwhelm your opponent with destruction effects and pure attack power. The Extra Deck in this build is mainly used as utility for the likes of Pot of Disparity, and Dogmatika Punishment, but we can also go into Rank 8s such as Dingirsu and Zombiestein (sometimes you just need a beater!). There's plenty of cards to help mill and search, such as Dark Spirit's Mastery, Void Apocalypse, Foolish Burial, and Danger! Mothman. The Dark Spirit monsters help revive your fiends and maintain pressure, whereas cards such as Skill Drain, Gozen Match and Mystic Mine help render your opponent powerless. Mystic Mine works very well with Archfiends, as they rely on destroying themselves. Therefore, you can pop cards on the field with monsters such as Archfiend Emperor, only for him to get destroyed as well, ensuring that you always have less monsters until you need to push for lethal! In addition, we also run 3 copies of Successor Soul and 2 copies of Zoa to send monsters rather than destroy. Since Archfiend Emperor destroys himself, you can use his effect to pop cards, then send an additional card through Successor Soul and then rewarding your efforts with a 2600 beatstick! Check out the deck profile here Enjoy, and until next time I'll see you around!

deck_excerpt: Paleo Frogs rely on a large number of traps, combined with the Frog archetype in order to disrupt the opponent and their plays.
deck_description: Paleo Frogs consist of the 9 best frog cards, and many traps (most of which are part of the Paleozoic archetype) in the Main Deck. Their main strategy is to disrupt the opponent's plays with cards like Infinite Impermanence, Paleozoic Canadia, Paleozoic Dinomischus,  and the Solemn series of counter traps. Using such a large amount of traps allows them to take advantage of the effects of the Paleozoic traps from the GY, which special summon them as level 2 aqua type monsters. This just so happens to coincide with Toadally Awesome's summoning conditions, which is a powerful negation card. However, there is a plethora of rank 2 XYZ monsters to take advantage of. Post Phantom Rage, the deck doesn't actually change much. I just wanted an excuse to post this. But, it does add the new TCG card, Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder, which is an incredible piece of XYZ support. While being slightly situational, its ability to nuke the field effortlessly can't be ignored.

deck_excerpt: Post Banlist "Domain Monarchs" deck with maximum possible consistency. Unlimitied Pantheism makes Pot of Desires a viable option.
deck_description:
I used to be a big fan of this archetype, having invested a lot of time and love into building my own version for a good couple of years, then stopped playing it during late 2018. That was the point where I realized that, even at full power, nothing but new support could ever bring the king of bricks back to their former glory; the meta is way faster, way more consistent, and with cards like Lightning Storm, Dark Ruler No More and Forbidden Droplet becoming the new powerful staples along Ash Blossom and Infinite Impermanence (which already gave Monarch players a pretty hard time to deal with), I'm confident that Domain Monarchs have been reduced to an archetype to play with, for fun, against your friends. That being said, since there's honestly no way to take consistent wins against more competitive decks, I decided to focus on making a build that is, at least, as consistent as it can get. You will still brick from time to time, it doesn't have a perfect search engine like other archetypes do, but at least you'll be able to do its main functions and get the feel that you're playing "pure" Monarchs.   The main differences between this and my previous build are:
  1. Having 3x copies of Pantheism allows for using Pot of Desires as a viable draw-card, without the danger of killing the only copy of the best card in the deck.
  2. Same goes for the Prime Monarch, where I have 2x copies this time around, which run better than 1x with an unlimited Pantheism, hence tribute fodder is better.
  3. Also, 3x copies of Ehther means easier to search, though running 6x lvl.8 Monarchs instead of 4x makes it slightly more dangerous to brick.
  4. Last but not least, running 2x copies of Majesty's instead of Vanity's suits Tenacity better, though I still believe that Tenacity is very occational and not that great of a card. Plus, the lack of Allure of Darkness opens slots for less Dark monsters, which is also a reason why I chose to run Mithra instead of Kaiser Vorse Raider; Pantheism and Desires bring more consistency, meaning you can more easily draw Monarchs and not rely on KVR's double nature.
  It's worth noting that I choose to main only 1x copy of Stormforth, as opening with even 1x when going first bricks hard. I save the remaining 2x copies for when going 2nd, while the rest of my Side Deck gives plenty of option to counter both monster-spams and spell/trap-spams.
